&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;img src="https://irp.cdn-website.com/088b40b3/dms3rep/multi/5-42925e83-538a7927.png" alt="Social media (see image)"/&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;" data-rss-type="text"&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;h2&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;span style="display: initial; color: rgb(89, 158, 202);"&gt;&#xD;
      
           8 - You’re missing out on Social Media
          &#xD;
    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;" data-rss-type="text"&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;p&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;span style="display: initial;"&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;span style="display: initial;"&gt;&#xD;
        
            No one doubts
           &#xD;
      &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;a href="/social-media-manager-old" style="display: initial;"&gt;&#xD;
      
           social media
          &#xD;
    &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;span style="display: initial;"&gt;&#xD;
      
           ’s importance in a modern marketing plan. If you don’t share your social channels on your main marketing channel - your website - how can visitors find you in the social sphere? Often, people are too lazy or fickle to start looking for themselves. Social media is an excellent tool for developing customer relations and promoting your brand. If your website is missing social buttons, be sure to add them. Also, it’s a good idea to check out your blog and add sharing buttons to each blog post.
           &#xD;
      &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;/p&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
